# For windosw
- open cmd, change directory to the folder that contains the Dockerfile
- windows change directory from C to D, "cd /d D-directory"
- then run docker 

- docker login
docker login
docker image ls

- build the image (pay attention to the space and period)
docker build -t manchen07/rvescd:v0 .

- check the docker image list
docker image ls

- check and test your app
docker run -d --rm -p 3838:3838 imageiddocker
localhost:3838 in your browser

- Check your packages 
docker run -ti imageID

- show all the packages in R
sessionInfo()

- push the image to DockerHub
docker push manchen07/rvescd:v0


# updates
- add required package into install_packages.R 
- go to terminal
- go to the directory, which has “Dockerfile”

# update v0 to v1
# cd at rvescdv1
docker images
docker build -t manchen07/rvescd:v1 .
docker push manchen07/rvescd:v1

# to remove from docker image
docker image rm -f imageID

